# 1. Variables

Variables are used to store data.

## let

* Can reassign ✅
* Cannot redeclare ❌

```javascript
let age = 20;
age = 21;
```

---

## const

* Cannot reassign ❌
* Cannot redeclare ❌

```javascript
const PI = 3.14;
```

---

## var

* Can reassign ✅
* Can redeclare ✅

```javascript
var age = 20;
var age = 21;
```

---

## Difference

| Keyword | Reassign | Redeclare |
| ------- | -------- | --------- |
| var     | ✅        | ✅         |
| let     | ✅        | ❌         |
| const   | ❌        | ❌         |

### Modern JavaScript Rule

* Use `const` by default.
* Use `let` when value changes.
* Avoid `var`.

