# Practice Problems Completed

## 1. Even/Odd Number

Concepts:

* Function
* if-else
* Modulus `%`

```javascript
function checkEvenOdd(number){
    if(number % 2 === 0){
        console.log("Even");
    }else{
        console.log("Odd");
    }
}
```

---

## 2. Largest of Three Numbers

Concepts:

* if-else-if
* Logical AND (`&&`)

```javascript
function largestOfThree(a, b, c){
    if(a > b && a > c){
        console.log(a);
    }else if(b > c){
        console.log(b);
    }else{
        console.log(c);
    }
}
```

---

## 3. Factorial

Concepts:

* Loop
* Multiplication Accumulator

```javascript
function factorial(num){
    let fact = 1;

    for(let i = 1; i <= num; i++){
        fact *= i;
    }

    console.log(fact);
}
```

---

## 4. Prime Number

Concepts:

* Loop
* Divisibility Check
* `return`

```javascript
function primeNumber(number){

    if(number <= 1){
        console.log("Not Prime");
        return;
    }

    for(let i = 2; i < number; i++){

        if(number % i === 0){
            console.log("Not Prime");
            return;
        }

    }

    console.log("Prime");
}
```

